still in command. Later he be- came praetor urbanus, and through Caesar’s influence propraetor of · Spain. He, however, joined the conspirators against Caesar’s life in 44 B.C. He was murdered in Syria in the same year by Dola- bella, being thus the first one of the liberatores to suffer for his connection with that plot. —— Fa- bium: another of Caesar’s legates in Gaul.
